this is called "America,
a Nation of Goddesses."

00:50:31.862 --> 00:50:34.114 align:middle line:84%
So far, all we're hearing
about is these men

00:50:34.114 --> 00:50:35.783 align:middle line:90%
who were the Venus families.

00:50:35.783 --> 00:50:37.409 align:middle line:84%
But you're saying
the feminine part

00:50:37.409 --> 00:50:38.869 align:middle line:84%
comes in because
they were devoted

00:50:38.869 --> 00:50:40.579 align:middle line:90%
to these feminine principles.

00:50:40.579 --> 00:50:41.531 align:middle line:90%
>> BUTLER: Absolutely.

00:50:41.531 --> 00:50:42.331 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:50:42.331 --> 00:50:44.833 align:middle line:84%
So I'm just trying to
get clear on that for any

00:50:44.833 --> 00:50:48.587 align:middle line:84%
of the women saying, I'm
looking for my story in here.

00:50:48.587 --> 00:50:54.426 align:middle line:84%
So we have these prominent
men, these Venus families,

00:50:54.426 --> 00:50:56.679 align:middle line:84%
devoted to these
feminine principles.

00:50:56.679 --> 00:51:00.599 align:middle line:84%
Now, we have arrived on
what will be American soil.

00:51:00.599 --> 00:51:03.852 align:middle line:84%
And we have the laying
out of Washington, DC.

00:51:03.852 --> 00:51:04.979 align:middle line:90%
So let's go for it there.

00:51:04.979 --> 00:51:06.610 align:middle line:84%
Then we're going
to go to the city

00:51:06.610 --> 00:51:10.192 align:middle line:84%
of-- as you call it, the city of
Osiris, which is New York City.

00:51:10.192 --> 00:51:11.735 align:middle line:90%
>> BUTLER: New York, yes.

00:51:11.735 --> 00:51:15.447 align:middle line:84%
Washington, DC, is
unique in that it's

00:51:15.447 --> 00:51:19.451 align:middle line:84%
one of very few cities in
the world which were planned

00:51:19.451 --> 00:51:22.162 align:middle line:84%
from scratch, and where,
therefore, the designers had

00:51:22.162 --> 00:51:26.125 align:middle line:84%
carte blanche to do
whatever they wanted to do.

00:51:26.125 --> 00:51:28.252 align:middle line:84%
What they started
out by doing was

00:51:28.252 --> 00:51:31.505 align:middle line:84%
to build something
which looks very

00:51:31.505 --> 00:51:36.635 align:middle line:84%
much like an ancient Olmec
or Mayan city, in that it

00:51:36.635 --> 00:51:40.055 align:middle line:84%
is deliberately,
astronomically-aligned

00:51:40.055 --> 00:51:42.099 align:middle line:90%
to the cardinal points.

00:51:42.099 --> 00:51:44.560 align:middle line:84%
And where the
buildings upon it were

00:51:44.560 --> 00:51:48.272 align:middle line:84%
placed in certain positions,
to do certain things

00:51:48.272 --> 00:51:52.901 align:middle line:84%
at certain times of year, to
go into an absolute detailed

00:51:52.901 --> 00:51:54.987 align:middle line:84%
explanation of all the
things that happened

00:51:54.987 --> 00:51:56.780 align:middle line:84%
would take us the
rest of the day.

00:51:56.780 --> 00:52:00.701 align:middle line:84%
But there's one thing which
really puts the lid on it,

00:52:00.701 --> 00:52:03.120 align:middle line:84%
and that is the
Washington Monument.

00:52:03.120 --> 00:52:07.499 align:middle line:84%
The Washington Monument is much
more than it appears to be.

00:52:07.499 --> 00:52:08.917 align:middle line:90%
It is where it.

00:52:08.917 --> 00:52:13.297 align:middle line:84%
Is the height it is because
it serves certain functions

00:52:13.297 --> 00:52:15.341 align:middle line:90%
throughout the year.

00:52:15.341 --> 00:52:21.180 align:middle line:84%
One of those functions is that
on the day of the Constitution,

00:52:21.180 --> 00:52:24.975 align:middle line:84%
or Constitution Day, as
the sun is going down,

00:52:24.975 --> 00:52:27.978 align:middle line:84%
it casts the shadow from
the Washington Monument that

00:52:27.978 --> 00:52:32.191 align:middle line:84%
goes right along the central
mall and just brushes

00:52:32.191 --> 00:52:34.902 align:middle line:84%
the Western doors
of the Capitol.

00:52:34.902 --> 00:52:37.529 align:middle line:84%
What's really
important about it is,

00:52:37.529 --> 00:52:40.282 align:middle line:84%
it could be said that those
who designed this to happen

00:52:40.282 --> 00:52:46.246 align:middle line:84%
were merely commemorating the
signing of the Constitution.

00:52:46.246 --> 00:52:50.709 align:middle line:84%
But that's also the day
of the Elysian ceremonies.

00:52:50.709 --> 00:52:54.380 align:middle line:84%
Now, this phenomena
takes place another time

00:52:54.380 --> 00:52:58.384 align:middle line:84%
during the year,
which is in March.

00:52:58.384 --> 00:53:04.014 align:middle line:84%
Now, there is no particular
anniversary for America itself

00:53:04.014 --> 00:53:05.849 align:middle line:90%
on that particular day.

00:53:05.849 --> 00:53:11.063 align:middle line:84%
But it's the date of the
rebirth of the god Attis.

00:53:11.063 --> 00:53:14.900 align:middle line:84%
And his story is just
a different version

00:53:14.900 --> 00:53:20.114 align:middle line:84%
of the retelling of the dying
and reborn god of the grain

00:53:20.114 --> 00:53:22.116 align:middle line:90%
and of the goddess.

00:53:22.116 --> 00:53:25.744 align:middle line:84%
So they have managed, clever
people that they were,

00:53:25.744 --> 00:53:27.996 align:middle line:84%
to build this monument
that does these two

00:53:27.996 --> 00:53:31.458 align:middle line:84%
very specific things on only
two days out of the year.

00:53:31.458 --> 00:53:34.169 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't do it
on any other day.

00:53:34.169 --> 00:53:39.174 align:middle line:84%
And they can say,
this means freedom.

00:53:39.174 --> 00:53:43.929 align:middle line:84%
When the edge of the shadow
touches the Western doors,

00:53:43.929 --> 00:53:47.808 align:middle line:84%
it confirms that
America is free,

00:53:47.808 --> 00:53:52.354 align:middle line:84%
that it doesn't have to kowtow
to the old medieval systems

00:53:52.354 --> 00:53:55.475 align:middle line:84%
and to all that went on
back in the old world.

00:53:55.475 --> 00:53:56.275 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: No.

00:53:56.275 --> 00:54:00.612 align:middle line:90%
We kowtow to Madison Avenue.

00:54:00.612 --> 00:54:03.991 align:middle line:84%
>> BUTLER: But the Washington
Monument itself does lots

00:54:03.991 --> 00:54:04.992 align:middle line:90%
of other things as well.

00:54:04.992 --> 00:54:09.538 align:middle line:84%
For example, just south
of the White House,

00:54:09.538 --> 00:54:12.819 align:middle line:84%
there is a huge
oval of land, which

00:54:12.819 --> 00:54:17.455 align:middle line:84%
is called the Ellipse--
very famous, big park.

00:54:17.455 --> 00:54:18.255 align:middle line:90%
It's elliptical.

00:54:18.255 --> 00:54:22.050 align:middle line:84%
And various ceremonies
take place there--

00:54:22.050 --> 00:54:23.469 align:middle line:90%
but it's open to the public.

00:54:23.469 --> 00:54:27.224 align:middle line:84%
And it used to be a series of
baseball-- >> REGINA: Diamonds.

00:54:27.224 --> 00:54:28.140 align:middle line:90%
>> BUTLER: --diamonds.

00:54:28.140 --> 00:54:28.390 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:54:28.390 --> 00:54:29.190 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:54:29.190 --> 00:54:30.601 align:middle line:90%
I'm English.

00:54:30.601 --> 00:54:32.686 align:middle line:90%
But now, it's just an open park.

00:54:32.686 --> 00:54:34.146 align:middle line:90%
But it's much more than that.

00:54:34.146 --> 00:54:36.023 align:middle line:90%
It has megalithic dimensions.

00:54:36.023 --> 00:54:37.399 align:middle line:84%
You remember the
megalithic yard?

00:54:37.399 --> 00:54:37.733 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:54:37.733 --> 00:54:37.900 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:54:37.900 --> 00:54:39.026 align:middle line:90%
>> BUTLER: It's measurable.

00:54:39.026 --> 00:54:42.321 align:middle line:84%
Right across-- 366
megalithic yards exactly.

00:54:42.321 --> 00:54:44.656 align:middle line:84%
So we looked to see what
happens with the shadow

00:54:44.656 --> 00:54:47.117 align:middle line:90%
from the Washington Monument.

00:54:47.117 --> 00:54:49.828 align:middle line:90%
It's absolutely uncanny.

00:54:49.828 --> 00:54:54.791 align:middle line:84%
On the 21st of December, which
we know is a pagan celebration,

00:54:54.791 --> 00:55:02.257 align:middle line:84%
the tip of the shadow just
grazes the side of the Ellipse.

00:55:02.257 --> 00:55:07.763 align:middle line:84%
And Janet was the first one
who said, this is meant to be.

00:55:07.763 --> 00:55:12.476 align:middle line:84%
This is what happens at
the midwinter solstice.

00:55:12.476 --> 00:55:15.521 align:middle line:84%
It is the meeting of
the god and the goddess.

00:55:15.521 --> 00:55:19.608 align:middle line:84%
It's the fertilization of the
Earth goddess by the sky god.

00:55:19.608 --> 00:55:25.155 align:middle line:84%
And they've symbolized
it through this shadow.

00:55:25.155 --> 00:55:28.742 align:middle line:84%
And I could go on and tell
you so many other things.

00:55:28.742 --> 00:55:31.230 align:middle line:84%
One thing I must mention--
tiny, little building

00:55:31.230 --> 00:55:35.040 align:middle line:84%
in the grounds of the Capitol
called the Summer House.

00:55:35.040 --> 00:55:36.708 align:middle line:84%
Hardly anybody even
knows it's there,

00:55:36.708 --> 00:55:38.877 align:middle line:84%
except the people who
work around there.

00:55:38.877 --> 00:55:40.546 align:middle line:84%
In the summer, they
may go there and sit

00:55:40.546 --> 00:55:41.547 align:middle line:90%
and have the sandwiches.

00:55:41.547 --> 00:55:43.687 align:middle line:84%
And there's a water
fountain in there,

00:55:43.687 --> 00:55:48.178 align:middle line:84%
so you can have a-- but this
particular building is probably

00:55:48.178 --> 00:55:51.098 align:middle line:84%
more fascinating than anything
else in Washington, DC,

00:55:51.098 --> 00:55:54.718 align:middle line:84%
because it's a veritable
observatory of Venus

00:55:54.718 --> 00:55:55.894 align:middle line:90%
and the Moon.

00:55:55.894 --> 00:55:59.314 align:middle line:84%
It has alignments all
over Washington, DC.

00:55:59.314 --> 00:56:01.233 align:middle line:84%
It was originally going
to be one of the pair.

00:56:01.233 --> 00:56:02.693 align:middle line:84%
There was going
to be two of them.

00:56:02.693 --> 00:56:04.236 align:middle line:84%
But the other one
never got built

00:56:04.236 --> 00:56:07.573 align:middle line:84%
because some of the senators
said, you've got one surmount.

00:56:07.573 --> 00:56:10.576 align:middle line:90%
You can't have another one.

00:56:10.576 --> 00:56:14.413 align:middle line:84%
And you can even work out
the longitude and latitude

00:56:14.413 --> 00:56:17.583 align:middle line:84%
of the moon by standing in
the entrance to this place.

00:56:17.583 --> 00:56:19.751 align:middle line:90%
It's just phenomenal.

00:56:19.751 --> 00:56:21.795 align:middle line:84%
And we keep finding
more and more things

00:56:21.795 --> 00:56:23.213 align:middle line:90%
all over Washington, DC.

00:56:23.213 --> 00:56:27.134 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Thank you so much
for making our capital mystical

00:56:27.134 --> 00:56:30.762 align:middle line:84%
and beautiful, and giving it
more dimension than most people

00:56:30.762 --> 00:56:31.597 align:middle line:90%
understand.

00:56:31.597 --> 00:56:35.225 align:middle line:84%
>> BUTLER: To me, it's the
most sacred city in the world,

00:56:35.225 --> 00:56:36.643 align:middle line:90%
without a shadow of a doubt.

00:56:36.643 --> 00:56:37.519 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: I love it.

00:56:37.519 --> 00:56:39.980 align:middle line:84%
>> BUTLER: It beats Rome and
Jerusalem into a [INAUDIBLE]

00:56:39.980 --> 00:56:43.025 align:middle line:84%
because it was deliberately
built that way.

00:56:43.025 --> 00:56:46.320 align:middle line:84%
And the fact that hardly
anybody knows it is great.

00:56:46.320 --> 00:56:47.946 align:middle line:84%
I shouldn't be here
talking to you now,

00:56:47.946 --> 00:56:48.989 align:middle line:90%
because it belongs to me.

00:56:48.989 --> 00:56:49.948 align:middle line:90%
It's mine.

00:56:49.948 --> 00:56:50.866 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh.

00:56:50.866 --> 00:56:52.993 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for sharing.

00:56:52.993 --> 00:56:55.414 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to ask you one more
question, while we're on it.

00:56:55.414 --> 00:56:57.289 align:middle line:84%
We'll go up a little
north to the city of New

00:56:57.289 --> 00:56:58.582 align:middle line:90%
York, the city of Osiris.

00:56:58.582 --> 00:56:59.958 align:middle line:84%
And tell us your
thoughts on that

00:56:59.958 --> 00:57:02.127 align:middle line:84%
and what you've observed
before we wrap it up.

00:57:02.127 --> 00:57:03.920 align:middle line:90%
>> BUTLER: OK.

00:57:03.920 --> 00:57:08.842 align:middle line:84%
One of the things about New
York is central station,

00:57:08.842 --> 00:57:12.512 align:middle line:84%
which everybody knows about--
fantastic-looking building.

00:57:12.512 --> 00:57:15.216 align:middle line:84%
And on the roof of New
York's Central-- >> REGINA:

00:57:15.216 --> 00:57:16.016 align:middle line:90%
Grand Central.

00:57:16.016 --> 00:57:19.728 align:middle line:84%
>> BUTLER: --Grand
Central-- is a star map.

00:57:19.728 --> 00:57:22.981 align:middle line:84%
Now, the star map shows all
the major constellations

00:57:22.981 --> 00:57:27.444 align:middle line:84%
of the Milky Way and of
the plane of the ecliptic.

00:57:27.444 --> 00:57:30.489 align:middle line:84%
But the problem is that
they're all back to front.

00:57:30.489 --> 00:57:33.241 align:middle line:84%
Nobody really understood
why they were back to front.

00:57:33.241 --> 00:57:35.786 align:middle line:84%
But all sorts of ideas
have been put forward

00:57:35.786 --> 00:57:39.289 align:middle line:84%
about how the architect made
projections from the floor.

00:57:39.289 --> 00:57:44.336 align:middle line:84%
And so everything ended up as
if the sky appeared on the West,

00:57:44.336 --> 00:57:47.297 align:middle line:84%
whereas in fact, it appears on
the East and turns that way.

00:57:47.297 --> 00:57:48.632 align:middle line:90%
But there is an exception.

00:57:48.632 --> 00:57:52.135 align:middle line:84%
And that exception is a
constellation called Orion.

00:57:52.135 --> 00:57:55.681 align:middle line:84%
Orion is the only constellation
on the ceiling of the station

00:57:55.681 --> 00:57:58.517 align:middle line:90%
that is the correct way round.

00:57:58.517 --> 00:58:01.019 align:middle line:84%
That could not have happened--
>> REGINA: By accident.

00:58:01.019 --> 00:58:02.354 align:middle line:90%
>> BUTLER: --by accident.

00:58:02.354 --> 00:58:04.731 align:middle line:84%
It's understandable that
they've got the whole thing back

00:58:04.731 --> 00:58:06.692 align:middle line:90%
to front, but not--

00:58:06.692 --> 00:58:09.611 align:middle line:84%
[INTERPOSING VOICES] >> REGINA:
--one aspect correct, yes.

00:58:09.611 --> 00:58:11.655 align:middle line:84%
>> BUTLER: So Janet
and I thought,

00:58:11.655 --> 00:58:13.156 align:middle line:84%
they're trying to
tell us something.

00:58:13.156 --> 00:58:14.700 align:middle line:84%
And we already
knew that Orion was

00:58:14.700 --> 00:58:18.682 align:middle line:84%
very important to our ancient
ancestors-- and, in particular,

00:58:18.682 --> 00:58:21.790 align:middle line:84%
part of Orion, which is called
Orion's Belt. Now, Orion's Belt

00:58:21.790 --> 00:58:24.710 align:middle line:84%
is three stars in a row, but
there's just a very slight dog

00:58:24.710 --> 00:58:25.794 align:middle line:90%
leg.

00:58:25.794 --> 00:58:27.379 align:middle line:84%
So you always know
when you're looking

00:58:27.379 --> 00:58:30.090 align:middle line:84%
at something that represents
Orion's Belt, because it

00:58:30.090 --> 00:58:31.007 align:middle line:90%
looks straight.

00:58:31.007 --> 00:58:32.634 align:middle line:84%
But if you look very
carefully, there's

00:58:32.634 --> 00:58:34.553 align:middle line:84%
a very slight dog
leg in the middle.

00:58:34.553 --> 00:58:39.391 align:middle line:84%
And we were looking at
other examples of obelisks

00:58:39.391 --> 00:58:42.728 align:middle line:90%
like the one in Washington, DC.

00:58:42.728 --> 00:58:50.235 align:middle line:84%
And Janet, god bless her,
found three particular obelisk.

00:58:50.235 --> 00:58:52.904 align:middle line:84%
The northernmost one
is in Central Park

00:58:52.904 --> 00:58:56.776 align:middle line:84%
and is truly Egyptian,
because it was brought across.

00:58:56.776 --> 00:58:57.576 align:middle line:90%
And it matches.

00:58:57.576 --> 00:58:59.327 align:middle line:90%
It's one of the pair.

00:58:59.327 --> 00:59:02.080 align:middle line:84%
And the other one is, like,
two minutes walk from here.

00:59:02.080 --> 00:59:04.040 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yes, it is--
right across the river.

00:59:04.040 --> 00:59:05.250 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:59:05.250 --> 00:59:07.878 align:middle line:84%
>> BUTLER: And I think you
call yours Cleopatra's Needle

00:59:07.878 --> 00:59:09.421 align:middle line:90%
as well, as we call ours.

00:59:09.421 --> 00:59:11.256 align:middle line:90%
But anyway, it's there.

00:59:11.256 --> 00:59:13.633 align:middle line:84%
And there are two much
more modern obelisks

00:59:13.633 --> 00:59:16.261 align:middle line:90%
as we come down Manhattan.

00:59:16.261 --> 00:59:20.098 align:middle line:84%
And I love to do graphics
and things like that there,

00:59:20.098 --> 00:59:21.975 align:middle line:90%
and very accurate measurements.

00:59:21.975 --> 00:59:24.936 align:middle line:84%
And so I put all these on
a map, and I measured them

00:59:24.936 --> 00:59:26.480 align:middle line:90%
as accurately as I could.

00:59:26.480 --> 00:59:31.536 align:middle line:84%
I took the positions of the
real Orion's Belt in the sky,

00:59:31.536 --> 00:59:34.237 align:middle line:90%
scaled it up, and placed it on.

00:59:34.237 --> 00:59:36.907 align:middle line:90%
And it's absolutely perfect.

00:59:36.907 --> 00:59:44.498 align:middle line:84%
They have recreated Orion's Belt
down the length of New York.

00:59:44.498 --> 00:59:50.496 align:middle line:84%
And the bottom of the three
is by St. Paul's Church-- >>

00:59:50.496 --> 00:59:51.296 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Mhm.

00:59:51.296 --> 00:59:52.096 align:middle line:90%
Cathedral.

00:59:52.096 --> 00:59:56.968 align:middle line:84%
>> BUTLER: --which is right
by ground zero, and somehow,

00:59:56.968 --> 00:59:59.971 align:middle line:90%
miraculously, survived.

00:59:59.971 --> 01:00:01.723 align:middle line:90%
And that really was a miracle.

01:00:01.723 --> 01:00:07.062 align:middle line:84%
So we know that the kind of
business which had gone on

01:00:07.062 --> 01:00:08.939 align:middle line:84%
in Washington, DC,
in terms of making

01:00:08.939 --> 01:00:13.652 align:middle line:84%
these places holy and
special, has been perpetuated

01:00:13.652 --> 01:00:15.695 align:middle line:90%
in other cities too.

01:00:15.695 --> 01:00:18.156 align:middle line:84%
And it's such a
big job that we are

01:00:18.156 --> 01:00:20.575 align:middle line:90%
opening new doors all the time.

01:00:20.575 --> 01:00:23.245 align:middle line:84%
There's obviously much more in
New York that we haven't seen.

01:00:23.245 --> 01:00:25.747 align:middle line:84%
The problem is that Washington
has so much that we keep

01:00:25.747 --> 01:00:27.165 align:middle line:90%
getting dragged back to it.

01:00:27.165 --> 01:00:29.793 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Oh, I wish you'd
just focus on San Francisco.

01:00:29.793 --> 01:00:33.088 align:middle line:84%
But I'm afraid we may not find
that there is a lot of people

01:00:33.088 --> 01:00:36.007 align:middle line:84%
who made some money in the
gold mining days, who ended up

01:00:36.007 --> 01:00:37.133 align:middle line:90%
on the Barbary Coast.

01:00:37.133 --> 01:00:39.261 align:middle line:84%
And other things
happened instead.

01:00:39.261 --> 01:00:40.846 align:middle line:90%
But we are out of time.

01:00:40.846 --> 01:00:43.682 align:middle line:84%
